        <section class="seo-content">
            <h2>Why Home Insulation Matters</h2>
            <p>Proper home insulation is one of the most cost-effective ways to improve your home's energy efficiency, comfort, and acoustics. Insulation creates a barrier that slows the transfer of heat. In the winter, it keeps the warmth generated by your heating system inside. In the summer, it prevents the hot exterior air from penetrating your living spaces, reducing the load on your air conditioning system.</p>
            <p>Beyond energy savings, good insulation also acts as a sound dampener, reducing noise transfer between rooms and blocking outside noise like traffic. It can also help control moisture accumulation by moving the dew point within wall cavities, preventing condensation and mold growth when paired with proper vapor retarders.</p>

            <h2>Understanding R-Value</h2>
            <p>The performance of insulation is measured by its <strong>R-value</strong>, which stands for resistance to heat flow. The higher the R-value, the greater the insulating power. The total R-value of a wall or ceiling is determined by the type of insulation, its thickness, and its density.</p>
            <p>It's important to note that compressing insulation (like cramming R-19 fiberglass meant for a 2x6 wall into a 2x4 cavity) actually <em>decreases</em> its R-value. Furthermore, gaps or voids in insulation can severely degrade performance. Continuous insulation, such as rigid foam board applied to the exterior of the studs, helps prevent "thermal bridging" where heat bypasses the cavity insulation through the wood framing itself.</p>

            <h2>How to Choose the Right Insulation</h2>
            <p>Selecting the best insulation for your project depends on several factors:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> Are you insulating an unfinished attic floor, existing enclosed walls, a damp crawlspace, or a cathedral ceiling? Blown-in cellulose is great for filling existing walls, while closed-cell spray foam is ideal for damp basement walls.</li>
                <li><strong>Climate:</strong> If you live in a cold climate (Zones 5-8), you need significantly higher R-values, especially in the attic, compared to someone living in Zone 1.</li>
                <li><strong>Budget:</strong> Fiberglass batts are generally the most affordable and DIY-friendly option. Spray foam provides exceptional performance and air sealing but comes at a premium price and usually requires professional installation.</li>
                <li><strong>Space Constraints:</strong> If you only have a 2x4 wall cavity (3.5 inches depth) but need a high R-value, you might need to use a denser material like closed-cell spray foam or continuous rigid foam on the exterior rather than standard fiberglass.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>

  <script is:inline>

        // Accordion functionality
        function toggleAccordion(button) {
            const item = button.parentElement;
            const content = item.querySelector('.accordion-content');

            item.classList.toggle('active');

            if (item.classList.contains('active')) {
                content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + "px";
            } else {
                content.style.maxHeight = "0";
            }
        }

        // Copy Table Data
        function copyTable(tableId) {
            const table = document.getElementById(tableId);
            let text = "Climate Zone | Uninsulated Attic | Existing Attic | Floors | Wood Frame Walls\n";
            text += "---|---|---|---|---\n";

            const rows = table.querySelectorAll('tbody tr:not(.hidden)');
            rows.forEach(row => {
                const cells = row.querySelectorAll('td');
                let rowData = [];
                cells.forEach(cell => {
                    // Extract text, handling the multiple badges in Zone 1/2 or 5/6 cleanly
                    let cellText = cell.innerText.replace(/\n/g, '/');
                    rowData.push(cellText);
                });
                text += rowData.join(" | ") + "\n";
            });

            navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
                const btn = document.getElementById('copy-table-btn');
                const originalText = btn.innerHTML;
                btn.innerHTML = `<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Copied!`;

                setTimeout(() => {
                    btn.innerHTML = originalText;
                }, 2000);
            }).catch(err => {
                console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
            });
        }

        // Search/Filter functionality
        function filterContent() {
            const searchInput = document.getElementById('searchInput');
            const filter = searchInput.value.toLowerCase();
            const searchItems = document.querySelectorAll('.search-item');
            const noResults = document.getElementById('no-results');

            let totalVisible = 0;
            let visibleTypes = 0;
            let visibleZones = 0;

            searchItems.forEach(item => {
                const keywords = item.getAttribute('data-keywords') || "";
                const text = item.innerText.toLowerCase();

                if (text.includes(filter) || keywords.includes(filter)) {
                    item.classList.remove('hidden');
                    totalVisible++;

                    if(item.classList.contains('card')) visibleTypes++;
                    if(item.tagName.toLowerCase() === 'tr') visibleZones++;
                } else {
                    item.classList.add('hidden');
                }
            });

            // Handle section headers visibility based on content
            const typeSectionElements = document.querySelectorAll('[data-section="types"]');
            typeSectionElements.forEach(el => {
                if (visibleTypes === 0) {
                    el.classList.add('hidden');
                } else {
                    el.classList.remove('hidden');
                }
            });

            const zoneSectionElements = document.querySelectorAll('[data-section="zones"]');
            zoneSectionElements.forEach(el => {
                if (visibleZones === 0) {
                    el.classList.add('hidden');
                } else {
                    el.classList.remove('hidden');
                }
            });

            // Show 'no results' message if needed
            if (totalVisible === 0) {
                noResults.style.display = 'block';
            } else {
                noResults.style.display = 'none';
            }
        }

  </script>
</SiteLayout>
